I tried multiple solutions to remove these annoying links in the windows explorer shell (win7 / 2008 R2), but none worked perfectly. But thanks to Appsense EM it&#8217;s pretty easy to get rid of these useless things.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" width="165" height="215" /> 

The trick is to create the apropriate actions for a &#8220;Process Starte&#8221; trigger. Just trigger explorer.exe. This will hold short the shell from initializing and performing the required actions.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" width="561" height="160" /> 

I have exported this configuration as a XML template. You can download it <a href="../images/2011/08/Tune_Explorer_Shell.zip" target="_blank">here</a> and import it into your EM policy.

Have fun!
